Sentencas: A composite material (hereafter referred to as NYC) containing Ni, Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 (YSZ) and Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-delta (CC10) particles was prepared and used as the anode of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: A Ni/YSZ composite containing Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-δ particles as an anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: The performance of NYC was better than that of conventional Ni/YSZ anodes in terms of anodic overpotential and interface impedance.
Titulo: A Ni/YSZ composite containing Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-δ particles as an anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: The additional CC10 particles improved the anode properties.
Titulo: A Ni/YSZ composite containing Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-δ particles as an anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: XRD results suggest that a solid solution of YSZ and CC10 was produced.
Titulo: A Ni/YSZ composite containing Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-δ particles as an anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: From impedance measurements, it is concluded that the solid solution exhibits substantial electronic conduction.
Titulo: A Ni/YSZ composite containing Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-δ particles as an anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: Ni/YSZ/15 wt% Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-delta anodes exhibited the best properties over the experimental temperature range.
Titulo: A Ni/YSZ composite containing Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-δ particles as an anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: A SOFC with an anode of Ni/YSZ/15 wt% Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-delta provided the maximum power density and current density.
Titulo: A Ni/YSZ composite containing Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-δ particles as an anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: Addition of CC10 with an average particle size of 0.3 mum was more advantageous than that with an average size of 3 mum.
Titulo: A Ni/YSZ composite containing Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-δ particles as an anode for SOFCs
